column4: 4. How often do you feel stressed due to your teaching workload?
column5: 5. How much pressure do you feel to publish research papers in high-ranking journals?
column6: 6. How much stress do you experience in fulfilling administrative responsibilities (e.g., meetings, paperwork)?
column7: 7. How often do you feel that your work is unrecognized or undervalued by your institution?
column8: 8. How much stress do you experience due to review of  faculty for promotions, awards, or recognition?
column9: 9. Do you believe that constant work-related stress is negatively impacting your physical health?
column10: 10. How often do you take sick leaves due to stress-related health problems?
column11: 11. How often do you feel your work-related stress negatively affects your interactions with relatives and friends?
column12: 12. How has stress impacted your ability to engage in social activities or hobbies?
column13: 13. How much does stress impact your ability to engage in meaningful personal relationships (e.g., spouse, children, friends)?
